President Obama has nominated Ronald W. Sharpe to serve as a U.S. Attorney for the District of the Virgin Islands. Sharpe has been serving as the interim U.S. Attorney for the district since 2009 and has previously worked as an Assistant U.S. Attorney in both the District of the Virgin Islands and the District of Columbia. He also worked as an Associate at Jones, Day, Reavis & Pogue law firm. Sharpe graduated from Tulane University in 1987 and Stanford Law School in 1991.